ZH: 1. 他不停地窃笑，但不敢发出声音。
EN: He kept chuckling silently, but dared not make any sound.
ZH: 2. 我注意到她偷偷地窃笑了一下。
EN: I noticed that she chuckled secretly for a moment.
ZH: 3. 他看到了那个有趣的画面，窃笑着掩嘴微笑。
EN: He saw the amusing scene and chuckled, covering his mouth with a smile.
ZH: 4. 当他们被捉弄时，他们窃笑着互相打趣。
EN: When they were teased, they chuckled and bantered each other.
ZH: 5. 她看到那个画面，窃笑起来，眼泪都笑出来了。
EN: She saw the scene, chuckled, and laughed till tears came out.
ZH: 6. 那个小丑表演得太有趣了，观众都在窃笑。
EN: The clown's performance was so funny that the audience chuckled.
ZH: 7. 学生们窃笑了一下，但很快就恢复了安静。
EN: The students chuckled for a moment, but quickly regained their silence.
ZH: 8. 他的那个笑话太搞笑了，我不禁窃笑。
EN: His joke was so funny that I couldn't help but chuckle.
ZH: 9. 当他绊倒时，我们窃笑了一下，但很快就跑过去帮助他了。
EN: We chuckled when he tripped, but quickly ran to help him.
ZH: 10. 她的傻举动让我们都窃笑出声。
EN: Her silly behavior made us all chuckle out.
ZH: 11. 我们窃笑着听着教授的幽默故事。
EN: We chuckled as we listened to the professor's humorous story.
ZH: 12. 她窃笑着挂断了电话。
EN: She chuckled and hung up the phone.
ZH: 13. 我看到他偷偷窃笑的样子，知道他在想些什么。
EN: I saw him chuckling secretly, knowing what he was thinking.
ZH: 14. 看到那部搞笑电影，他们不停地窃笑。
EN: They chuckled nonstop while watching the hilarious movie.
ZH: 15. 他窃笑着将伸错入口袋。
EN: He chuckled as he put his hand into the wrong pocket.
ZH: 16. 面对困难，他总能带着窃笑应对。
EN: He always faces difficulties with a chuckle.
ZH: 17. 我窃笑了一下，然后继续做我的工作。
EN: I chuckled for a moment, then continued with my work.
ZH: 18. 这个笑话太搞笑了，我们全班一起窃笑。
EN: This joke is so funny that the whole class chuckled together.
ZH: 19. 当他们跳着欢快的舞蹈时，观众都在窃笑。
EN: The audience chuckled as they danced joyfully.
ZH: 20. 她的幽默引发了我们的窃笑，让场面更加轻松愉快。
EN: Her humor triggered our chuckles, making the atmosphere more relaxed and enjoyable.
